  <summary>4/6/1995--Introduced.
Commends the Government of India for its commitment to religious pluralism and tolerance. Recognizes: (1) such Government for its willingness to give refuge to displaced victims of religious persecution; and (2) the contributions of India to the cause of religious harmony throughout the world.</summary>
